cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper is primarily focused on predicting cyber attacks using machine learning techniques based on deep neural networks and autoregressive time series models. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of external signals from publicly available web sources, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of data from various web sources, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
